context: The <a0_0><b6_0>Duke Energy Center for the Performing Arts<a0_0/> complex<b6_0/> houses the Raleigh Memorial Auditorium, the <a1_0>Fletcher Opera Theater<a1_0/>, the Kennedy Theatre, and the Meymandi Concert Hall. In <a2_0><b5_0>2008<b5_0/><a2_0/>, a new theatre space, the <b7_0><b8_0>Meymandi Theatre<b8_0/><b7_0/> at the <b9_0>Murphey School<b9_0/>, was opened in the restored auditorium of the historic Murphey School. Theater performances are also offered at the <a3_0>Raleigh Little Theatre<a3_0/>, Long View Center, Ira David Wood III Pullen Park Theatre, and <a4_0>Stewart and Thompson Theaters<a4_0/> at North Carolina State University.
